HOUSE RESOLUTION 178
By Lamberth
A RESOLUTION to commend Ella Muncy for exemplary service
as a legislative intern for the Tennessee Board
of Regents.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, we are pleased to recognize certain persons who
have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the legislative
process; and
WHEREAS, Ella Muncy is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her role
as a legislative intern with the Tennessee Board of Regents; Ms. Muncy's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for the staff of the Tennessee Board of Regents she assisted and the
operation of the agency as a whole; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Muncy earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Political Science and Global
Studies from the University of Tennessee in 2023 and a Master of Arts degree in International
Studies and Diplomacy in 2025; and
WHEREAS, during her undergraduate career, Ella Muncy was a member of the Alpha
Omicron Pi Sorority and Leading Women of Tomorrow; through the Council on International
Educational Exchange, she participated in a study abroad program in London, England, where
she studied global environmental policy and international political systems; and
WHEREAS, a leader in her community, Ms. Muncy currently serves as a teacher at
Children First Preschool, supporting the social, emotional, and cognitive development of young
children and designing engaging activities to stimulate early literacy and numeracy skills; she
previously served the YMCA of East Tennessee as an after-school counselor for students in
grades kindergarten through five; and
HR0178
016982
- 1 -

WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government, Ms. Muncy brought her many abilities and singular expertise to
Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred Fourteenth General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, throughout the 2026 legislative session, Ella Muncy has surpassed all
criteria that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Muncy has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby
commend Ella Muncy for outstanding service as a legislative intern for the Tennessee Board of
Regents and extend to her our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
